y called the Refrainzeilerefrain line lyric the beginning end section that repeated every iteration this usage the refrain does not constitute discrete independent section within the form large number TinPan Alley songs using thirtytwo bar form are central the traditional jazz repertoire jazz arrangements the word chorus refers the same unit music the Tin Pan Alley tradition but unlike the Tin Pan Alley tradition single song can have more than one chorus Von Appen and FreiHauenschild explain The term chorus can also refer single iteration the entire bars the AABA form especially among jazz musicians who improvise over multiple repetitions such choruses jazz arrangers chorus where the arranger uses particularly elaborate techniques exhibit his her skill and impress the listener This may include use counterpoint reharmonization tone color any other arranging device The arrangers chorus generally not the first the last chorus jazz performancecitation needed jazz shout chorus occasionally out chorus usually the last chorus Big Band arrangement and characterized being the most energetic lively and exciting and containing the musical climax the piece shout chorus characteristically employs extreme ranges loud dynamics and rearrangement melodic motives into short accented riffs Shout choruses often feature tutti concerted writing but may also use contrapuntal writing call and response between the brass and saxophones between the ensemble and the drummer Additionally brass players frequently use extended techniques such falls doits turns and shakes add excitement 